data: {"type":"response.output_item.done","item":{"type":"fabric_dataagent_preview_call_output","id":"fco_03078f13dba8de3a00699892751c2c8195bfcce34872ec2052","agent_reference":{"type":"agent_reference","name":"MyAgent","version":"247"},"response_id":"resp_03078f13dba8de3a0069989258e3288195bc2b9de42c51a14a","call_id":"call_8e0fa8b8b346406991dceaafb5ac2aa7","output":"{\"documents\":[{\"id\":\"1d870cf9-3eef-46ac-9112-1cabf821d0d3\",\"content\":\"Here are some notable recent weather events in Texas:\\n\\n- **High Winds (Dec 30\\u201331, 2007):** Gusts up to 71 mph at McDonald Observatory (Davis Mountains). No injuries or property damage reported.\\n- **Heavy Snow (Dec 27\\u201328, 2007):** Four inches of snow near Perryton and Spearman. Hazardous road conditions, but no injuries reported.\\n- **Tornadoes (Dec 27, 2007):** Observed near Slaton/Southland and north of Lubbock. No damage reported.\\n- **Fatal Winter Weather Accident (Dec 27, 2007):** Snow and icy conditions on US 287 near the Canadian River Bridge led to a rollover; one death and three injuries.\\n- **Major Winter Storm Accident (Dec 22, 2007):** Heavy snow and blowing wind caused whiteout conditions and multi-car accidents near Amarillo and Pampa. Two fatalities, over 150 injuries, and more than $1.6 million in property losses.\\n\\nIf you need events from a specific period, location, or event type, please specify!\\n\",\"filepath\":\"fabric://response\",\"title\":\"Fabric Response for: weather events in Texas\",\"url\":\"https://msit.fabric.microsoft.com/groups/409e30ce-b2ad-4c80-a54d-d645227322e4/aiskills/98042b9e-11cb-422d-bd97-5873411aa7c8/stage/published/threads/thread_MuEWccMsL1Y7Q2gTKDe0QxyT/runs/run_fabjKA3y8GcHgBTVDGbnclY7zcC8/question/msg_QW5sReONh7TfjfhC8nEsZoZt/source/foundry\",\"metadata\":\"{\\u0022source\\u0022:\\u0022azure_fabric\\u0022,\\u0022query\\u0022:\\u0022weather events in Texas\\u0022,\\u0022data_agent_url\\u0022:\\u0022https://msit.fabric.microsoft.com/groups/409e30ce-b2ad-4c80-a5